OL,4,Cstate pension communication
OL,5,Ccompensation plans
OL,7,FThe letter continued: "The evidence we
OL,8,Freceived indicated support for a rules-
OL,9,Fbased system. This would be a system
OL,10,Fwhere payments would be adjusted
OL,11,Fwithin a range (based on the PHSO's
OL,12,Fseverity of injustice scale) to
OL,13,Freflect the extent of change in the
OL,14,Findividual's state pension age and the
OL,15,Fnotice of the change which the
OL,16,Findividual received.
OL,18,F"This would mean that the less notice
OL,19,Fyou had of the change and the bigger
OL,20,Fthe change in your SPA, the higher the
OL,21,Fpayment you would receive.
OL,26,@oD@WOUzD@AOU
