OL,7,F"While not perfect, the advantages of
OL,8,Fsuch a system are that it would be:
OL,9,Fquick to administer; applying known
OL,10,Fdata to a formula to determine the
OL,11,Famount due; and relatively
OL,12,Finexpensive."
OL,14,FThe letter also urged some flexibility
OL,15,Ffor people to make the case
OL,16,Findividually, after they have received
OL,17,Fthe payment using the rules-based
OL,18,Fsystem, that they experienced direct
OL,19,Ffinancial loss and that they are due a
OL,20,Fhigher level of compensation.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@MO]
