OL,4,Cstate pension communication
OL,5,Ccompensation plans
OL,7,F"While the ombudsman has put the
OL,8,Fmatter in the hands of Parliament, a
OL,9,Fremedy can only happen with the
OL,10,Fsupport of the Government and we hope
OL,11,Fministers will move quickly to bring
OL,12,Fforward its proposal before the
OL,13,Fsummer."
OL,15,FCommenting on the committee's actions,
OL,16,FMs Madden said: "Parliament's top
OL,17,Fpensions thinkers have spoken. It is
OL,18,Fnow time for the Government to act and
OL,19,Fgive the Commons as a whole its say.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@HO]xD@QOU
